	copyright = {All rights reserved},
	number = {3},
	html ={https://doi.org/10.6052/1000-0992-22-006},
	abstract={Non-spherical particle-laden flows are commonly seen and important in nature and industrial
	processes. The particle's rotational and orientational behaviors could affect the forces and torques
	acting on the particle from ambient fluid flow. To accurately capture the motion of non-spherical
	particles, especially for angular particle dynamics, most numerical studies of non-spherical particleladen
	flows are carried out in the Euler-Lagrange frame. There are two most popular numerical approaches:
	the point-particle method and the particle-resolved method. This paper comprehensively and
	systematically summarizes these methods and significant recent findings about non-spherical particles
	in simple and turbulent flows. The mechanism of particle orientation and rotation by suspended nonspherical
